description: Mingma Sherpa and Jyoti Manandhar, natives of Nepal and owners of Momo Crave in Woodside, experiment with recipes to gratifying results.
title: Playing With Tradition in Queens
title_page: Playing With Tradition in Queens - The New York Times
text: At Momo Crave on the border of Woodside and Jackson Heights, Queens, momos (dumplings) come deep-fried and thrust on skewers, tasting earthy and fervid, like tandoori chicken.
